                    <head>
                        <lb/>Embleme 31. Of the Secrets of Nature.
                        <lb/>The King swimming in the Sea cryes out with a loud voyce, hee that
                        <lb/>will deliver mee shall have great reward.
                    </head>
                </div>
                
                
                <div type="epigram" xml:lang="en">
                    <head>Epigramme 31.</head>
                    <lg>
                        <l>The King oppressed with a weighty Crowne,</l>
                        <l>Floting ith Sea, and being like to drowne,</l>
                        <l>Cryes out for helpe, O helpe without delay,</l>
                        <l>And I wish thanks your service will repay:</l>
                        <l>Be wise, and to my kingdoms mee restore,</l>
                        <l>That I may favour shew to rich and poore.</l>
                    </lg>
                </div>
                
                
                <pb n="99"/> <!-- Change to page number of the actual manuscript -->
